{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "For any possibility model M based on a standard possibility frame:1.",
    "M, x ⊩ ♢ i 1... ♢ in φ iff ∀x ′ ⊑ x ∃y ′ 1,..., y ′ n: x ′ R i 1 y ′ 1... y ′ n-1 R in y ′ n and M, y ′ n ⊩ φ; 2.",
    "M, x ⊩ □ j ♢ i 1... ♢ in φ iff∀y, if xR j y, then ∃y 1,..., y n: yR i 1 y 1... y n-1 R in y n and M, y n ⊩ φ.",
    "For part 1, in the truth condition for ¬□ i 1... □ in ¬φ given above, together y ′ n-1 R in y ′ n and ∃y ′′ n ⊑ y ′ n imply y ′ n-1 R in y ′′ n by the R-down property of standard frames.",
    "For part 2, by part 1 we have that M, x ⊩ □ j ♢ i 1... ♢ in φ iff ∀y, if xR j y, then ∀y ′ ⊑ y ∃y ′ 1,..., y ′ n: y ′ R i 1 y ′ 1... y ′ n-1 R in y ′ n and M, y ′ n ⊩ φ.This clearly implies the clause given in part 2, and the converse implication also holds due to R-down: for xR j y and y ′ ⊑ y together imply xR j y ′."
  ],
